Hi,

Wandering into godot code, I reached [Variant::can_convert](https://github.com/godotengine/godot/blob/master/core/variant.cpp#L432):

``` c++
bool Variant::can_convert(Variant::Type p_type_from,Variant::Type p_type_to) {
    ...
    const Type *valid_types=NULL;
    const Type *invalid_types=NULL;
    ...
    // set valid_types or invalid_types
    ...
    if (valid_types) {
        ...
    } else if (invalid_types) {
        int i=0;
        while(invalid_types[i]!=NIL) {
            if (p_type_from==invalid_types[i])
                return false;
            i++;
        }
    }
    return false;
}
```

It seems if `valid_types` is empty, `can_convert` can only return `false` no matter what `invalid_types` is.
I have the felling something's wrong here, isn't it ? :smile:

**Operating system or device - Godot version:**
2.x

**Issue description** (what happened, and what was expected):

It could be handy if we could modify the content of an `Image` by writing directly into the `RawArray` returned by `Image.get_data();` in gdscript.

**Steps to reproduce:**

```
var img = Image( 320, 200, false, Image.FORMAT_GRAYSCALE );

print( img.get_data()[ 456 ] );

img.get_data()[ 456 ] = 123;

print( img.get_data()[ 456 ] );
```

